# 5. 私はいい子

Teacher: Ms. Asahina. Could I speak with you for a moment?
Mafuyu: Ma'am? What is it?
Teacher: I wanted to know if you'd be interested in submitting the short essay you wrote for class to a competition.
Mafuyu: What? My essay?
Teacher: Yes. It was thematically sound and the other teachers all agree that it was well-written.
Mafuyu: It really wasn't anything special, but I'd be happy to do it if you think I should.
Teacher: I do. I'll go ahead and submit it for you, then.
Mafuyu: Okay, thank you.
Classmate A: Mafuyu! I heard about your essay! Way to go!
Classmate B: Yeah! Knowing you, you'll probably get an award!
Mafuyu: Haha, I don't know about that. I'm sure the other essays will be really good as well.
Mafuyu: More importantly...the fact that you're showering me with compliments all of a sudden means you're about to ask me for a favor, doesn't it?
Classmate A: Oh, busted... Please, help us with our studies again today, Lady Mafuyu!
Mafuyu: Hehe. Thought so. The homework we got today looks pretty hard, after all. Alright. Today was only a half day, so let's study together.
Classmate A: Thank you! You're a lifesaver!
Classmate B: Thank you, Mafuyu!
Classmate A: My head feels like it's going to burst! Can we take a break?
Mafuyu: We haven't even been at it an hour, you know.
Mafuyu: I guess this is pretty hard, though. A short break might be a good idea.
Classmate A: Yay!
Classmate A: Mafuyu, you're so nice. You never get upset and you never brag about having good grades or being good at sports!
Classmate B: Yeah. Sometimes it's hard to believe people like you actually exist!
Mafuyu: Oh, stop. What is it you want this time?
Classmate B: No more favors! Honest! I do feel a little bad, though. Are you sure you're okay always helping us like this?
Mafuyu: Huh?
Classmate A: Yeah! Mafuyu, you always go out of your way to do what we ask, but you never really ask for anything in return.
Classmate B: Yeah. We'd be happy to do something you'd like to do, you know.
Mafuyu: Something I'd like to do?
Mafuyu: Hm... I want everyone else to do what they want to do. Seeing others happy makes me happy.
Classmate A: Ack! The light! It's blinding! She's not an angel, she's a goddess!
Classmate B: Mafuyu! Why couldn't I have been born as your little sister!
Mafuyu: Ah! Watch out! You can't just glom onto people like that.
Mafuyu: Alright, you two. Break time's over. Time to get back to studying.
Classmate A & B: Yes, ma'am!
Mafuyu: Alright...
[Amia]: <Oh, Yuki? You're here. How's it going?>
[Yuki]: <Amia? I'm not used to seeing you on this early.>
[Amia]: <My usual shift at work was changed to tomorrow, so I was getting some stuff done.>
[Amia]: <I didn't think you were usually on this time of day either.>
[Yuki]: <I had a short day at school today, so I thought I'd get some work done I can't usually do on weekdays.>
[Amia]: <You sure are serious about all this, aren't you?>
[Yuki]: <No more than anybody else. You all work so hard, so I'm just trying to do my part as well.>
Mafuyu's Mother: I'm going to the store. I was thinking of making cream stew for dinner. What do you think?
[Yuki]: <Sorry, Amia. Give me a minute.>
[Amia]: <Sure thing.>
Mafuyu: That sounds great. Thanks, Mom.
Mafuyu's Mother: Okay, cream stew it is. Oh, how'd your study session with your friends go today?
Mafuyu: It was fun. They were really happy when the stuff they didn't understand finally started to click.
Mafuyu's Mother: That's nice. Just remember to say no to something if it's too much of an inconvenience, even if they are your friends.
Mafuyu: Huh?
Amia: <.....>
Mafuyu's Mother: You'd be better off spending time with people who can challenge you rather than those who always need your help. That way you'd actually be learning something as well.
Mafuyu's Mother: Make sure you're valuing your own time.
Mafuyu: Okay, I will.
Mafuyu's Mother: Anyway, I'll be back in a little while.
[Amia]: <Yuki, was that your mom just now?>
[Yuki]: <Yeah. Sorry about that.>
[Amia]: <No, don't mention it. I feel like I should be the one apologizing for eavesdropping.>
[Amia]: <But what she just said... Did she mean she didn't want you to be friends with kids who struggle at school?>
[Yuki]: <Well, I think she meant it more as advice to try and study with the smarter kids from time to time.>
[Amia]: <I guess you could also take it like that, but...>
[Amia]: <It sounds more like she's saying to pick your friends better. That doesn't bother you?>
[Amia]: <I don't think I'd like it very much if somebody tried to push their own values on me or told me their way of doing things was better.>
[Amia]: <Oh, I'm not saying that's what your mom was doing, though.>
[Yuki]: <.....>
[Amia]: <Yuki? You okay?>
[Yuki]: <Oh, yeah, I'm fine. That kind of stuff doesn't really bother me, I guess. I was just thinking how people can view these things differently.>
[Amia]: <I see. Everybody's different, I guess. If it doesn't bother you, then great. Oh, sorry for talking so long. I should get back to work.>
[Yuki]: <I should get some work done, too.>
[Yuki]: <Phew... This seems like a good place to stop for now.>
Mafuyu's Mom's Voice: Dinner's ready!
Mafuyu: Okay!
[Yuki]: <Amia, I'm going to log off for a while. I'll be back on later tonight.>
[Amia]: <Okay! Later!>
Mafuyu: This looks delicious! Thanks Mom.
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. Eat up while it's warm, honey.
Mafuyu's Father: Mm.
Mafuyu's Father: Mafuyu, you're entering your second year at school this year. How are your university entrance exam studies going?
Mafuyu: They're going just fine. Prep school is actually pretty fun.
Mafuyu's Mother: It'd be great if your dream of becoming a doctor came true. I'm sure you'll get into whatever university you want, but you should probably choose which one you like best soon.
Mafuyu: Which one I like best...
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes. Your father and I took the liberty of gathering some materials from a few schools we think would be good. You should look through them later.
Mafuyu's Father: They're all schools that'll help you learn to your full potential.
Mafuyu: Oh, thanks.
Mafuyu's Mother: The decision is up to you, though. You could even study abroad if that's what you want. If there's anything you want to discuss, just let us know.
Mafuyu's Father: That's right. You should do whatever it is you want to, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu's Mother: Just make sure you give it plenty of thought, okay?
Mafuyu's Father: Hey now, stop babying Mafuyu. She's more than capable of making her own decisions.
Mafuyu's Father: She's our pride and joy, after all.
Mafuyu: .....
Mafuyu: Yes, you're right. Don't worry, I'll think it through carefully.
Mafuyu: .....
Mafuyu: So annoying...
Teacher: Great job as usual, Ms. Asahina.
Classmate: We'd be happy to do something you'd like to do, you know.
Mafuyu's Mother: Just make sure you give it plenty of thought, okay?
Mafuyu's Father: She's our pride and joy, after all.
Mafuyu: What I want to do...
Mafuyu: Does such a thing even exist?
Mafuyu: I just don't know...
Miku: Mafuyu.
Mafuyu: Miku...
Mafuyu: I wish I could just stay in SEKAI forever.
